Often confused with cultists, misguided heretics, or crazed fanatics,
the Priests of Set dedicate their lives to a ambitious pursuit of
power. They gain this power through a series of bargains with Set,
the god of Chaos. These priests are terrifying in combat, mixing
heavy-hitting blows with the divine dominance of their god.

Priests typcially opt for scale or banded armor, forgoing full plate
for the rush of battle. For weapons, priests vary from dual-wielding
daggers to large blunt polearms.

The guild has two main abilities that all initiates learn: Bolt and
Mend. Bolt sacrifices some of the caster's own vitality to Set,
which is rewarded with a devastating attack on a foe. Similarly,
Mend uses some of the caster's vitality to restore health over time
for a target.

Trained priests learn other divine abilities, several of which
empower Bolt and Mend. Priests value wisdom over all attributes so
that they can strengthen their connection with Set. They also focus
on charisma to get their way and to guide others, and constitution
so that they can make more powerful bargains.

